50|$|By this time, Lärka {{started his}} lecturing tours. They started as picture shows {{for friends and}} others in the villages around Siljan, {{with the help of a}} {{so-called}} <b>sciopticon.</b> It was the first time many in the audience had experienced any of the forerunners of cinema. After a while the activity grow larger and Lärka's lecture tours were included in tours organised from Stockholm, with many lecturers involved. Lärka lectured during 1920 all over Sweden, often dressed in Sollerö costume and sometimes together with the folk musician Axel Myrman.|$|E

